 <h2><u>Plane of Disease</u></h2><br><br>Soloing the Plane of Disease can be good exp. However, there is better exp to be had at more demanding camps, and if you find yourself polishing everything off very easily, simply move elsewhere. It all depends on level, skill and mana.<br><br><br>Flies give 1% or more AA, and can be killed with very little risk. Its not unusual to run out of mobs before mana, and if you find yourself with nothing to kill then your better off attempting harder mobs.<br><br><br><br></center><b><u>Zone Information:</u></b><br><br><a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='moblist(163); return false;'>Plane of Disease (PoD) mob list</a><br>
<a href='http://www.eqmages.com' onClick='questlist(163); return false;'>Plane of Disease (PoD) quest list</a><br><a href='http://www.eqatlas.com/planes/planeofdiseasemap.html'>Plane of Disease (PoD) Map</a><br><br><b><u>Comments/Feedback:</u></b><br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>I solo in plane of disease all the time.  I don't bother with the fly's, I go to a spot near all the rat's, goo, larvae, and spiderlings.

At FT 10, DPoC focused Epic pet, 150 AA, and full focus effects I net around 1 AA in 2 hours there.  Considering there is no setup time, and it's pretty safe, I would say PoD soloing is one of my best spots when I need safe soloing for any length of time.  Stick on your LFG tag, and head to the spot.

I also completed the bangle of disease warding quest while camping in this zone.  It's a general slot insta-clicky item that gives +40 Disease resist.  You can cast on yourself or others.  I use it for resists, and on mobs that dispell.  There are 4 rare mobs, each with placeholders.  Kill the 4 named, loot 4 fleshes, then turn them in to an Ogre NPC wandering the zone called Grimror.  The PH for the named are not Larvae, they are Larva.

Malarian Larva---> Harrion Larva (drops Harrion Flesh)
Planarian Larva---> Sengian Larva (drops Sengian Flesh)
Planarian Larva---> Generian Larva (drops Generian Flesh)
Tetse Pupa---> Scaevian Larva (drops Scaevian Flesh)<br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>I just made the above comment.  I included spaces and such for formatting, but they don't show  :(  Anyways, email me if you want more info on this, I have an edited JPEG map somewhere I can send you and more info on the soloing spot.  It's a nice spot :)<br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>bah, email didn't show up either...  Ok, here is the address just typed out eandori@comcast.net<br><br><i><b>Anonymous</b> says:</i><br>doh, edit your address to read eandori at comcast dot net.  We will figure it out.  Leave it like it is and your inbox will get hammered with spam.<br><br><i><b>merloo</b> says:</i><br>nice work on the post, but are there any tips  for a level 63 not epicd mage with 40 aa's. ide apreciate any  help you folks  could give me.<br><br><i><b>Eandori Raintree</b> says:</i><br>I did a write up on that solo spot, here's a link!  
